      • addSecKeyCryptoAttr

        public KeyGenAlgorithmParaSpec.Builder addSecKeyCryptoAttr​(int secKeyCryptoAttrType,
                                                           String... attrs)
        Sets the values for the cryptographic attributes of a key, including the block cipher mode, padding mode, and digest algorithm.
        Parameters:
        secKeyCryptoAttrType - Indicates the cryptographic attribute type, which can be KeyStoreConstants#CRYPTO_PARAMETER_DIGEST, KeyStoreConstants#CRYPTO_PARAMETER_ENCRYPT_PADDING, KeyStoreConstants#CRYPTO_PARAMETER_BLOCK_MODE, or KeyStoreConstants#CRYPTO_PARAMETER_SIGNATURE_PADDING.
        attrs - Indicates the attribute set.
        Returns:
        Returns the Builder object.

      • setSecKeyAuthDuration

        public KeyGenAlgorithmParaSpec.Builder setSecKeyAuthDuration​(int secKeyAuthDuration)
        Sets the validity period of user authentication for a key.

        This method is valid only for keys that require user authentication to become accessible.

        Parameters:
        secKeyAuthDuration - Indicates the validity period of user authentication. By default, do not set it to -1.
        Returns:
        Returns the Builder object.
        Since:
        1

      • setSecKeySizeInBits

        public KeyGenAlgorithmParaSpec.Builder setSecKeySizeInBits​(int secKeySizeInBits)
        Sets the length of the generated key.

        The default key length will be used if secKeySizeInBits is not set.

        Parameters:
        secKeySizeInBits - Indicates the length of the generated key in bits. For example, the default length of an AES key is 128 bits.
        Returns:
        Returns the Builder object.
        Since:
        1

      • setSecKeyUsagePurposes

        public KeyGenAlgorithmParaSpec.Builder setSecKeyUsagePurposes​(int secKeyUsagePurposes)
        Sets the purposes for using a key.

        Examples include encryption, decryption, signing, and signature verification.

        Parameters:
        secKeyUsagePurposes - Indicates the purposes for using the key, which can be KeyStoreConstants#PURPOSE_CAN_ENCRYPT, KeyStoreConstants#PURPOSE_CAN_DECRYPT, KeyStoreConstants#PURPOSE_CAN_SIGN, or KeyStoreConstants#PURPOSE_CAN_VERIFY.
        Returns:
        Returns the Builder object.
        Since:
        1

        The algorithm parameters depend on the key type.

      • setSecKeyAccessibleAttr

        Parameters:
